race.comment: FUSION BLAZER (2) used the inside to advantage when a maiden winner two back then drew wider last time and could manage only sixth, beaten 10 lengths (19.19) at Richmond over 320m. Returns to the scene of his maiden win. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. ARCTIC JACKIE (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (20.36) in a Grade 5 at Gunnedah. Key runner on best form. LUMEAH TAYLOR (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing eighth (19.64) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Has ability and is one of the better chances. SCOTCH ALL ROUND (4) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.
